"Surprisingly full bodied for the style with a blast of dank, sticky hops giving off strong dry bitterness that lingers over the yeast and sweet malt notes into a dry finish. Â Hop flavor is a bit one dimensional with bitter earthy character. Â Lots of grass, pine needle and spruce tip with very little of the citrus/tropical fruit notes found in the nose. Â It's there providing subtle sweetness but is overpowered by bitterness and strong malt flavors. Â Hop bitterness is countered by bready yeast and malt sweetness. Â Lots of caramel, bread, toffee and nut. Â Well balanced with some nice hop flavor but it's not really light or easy drinking and doesn't really feel like a pale ale."
